1. The "Nuke" (Clean the Build Directory)

Since your .pro file defines a central directory for all build-related files, resetting is much easier for you than for most users. You just need to delete that directory:

Bash

rm -rf build/

    This removes all the object files (OBJECTS_DIR).

This removes the generated MOC, RCC, and UI files.

This ensures no "ghost" Ninja files or old Makefiles remain to confuse the compiler.
